card0.name: Pikachu
card0.description: Pikachu that can generate powerful electricity have cheek sacs that are extra soft and super stretchy.

card1.name: Charizard
card1.description: It spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. It may cause forest fires by blowing flames.

card2.name: Bulbasaur
card2.description: A strange seed was planted on its back at birth. The plant sprouts and grows with this POKéMON.

card3.name: Squirtle
card3.description: After birth, its back swells and hardens into a shell. Powerfully sprays foam from its mouth.

card4.name: Caterpie
card4.description: Its short feet are tipped with suction pads that enable it to tirelessly climb slopes and walls.

card5.name: Weedle
card5.description: Often found in forests, eating leaves. It has a sharp venomous stinger on its head.

card6.name: Pidgey
card6.description: A common sight in forests and woods. It flaps its wings at ground level to kick up blinding sand.

card7.name: Rattata
card7.description: Bites anything when it attacks. Small and very quick, it is a common sight in many places.

card8.name: Spearow
card8.description: Eats bugs in grassy areas. It has to flap its short wings at high speed to stay airborne.

card9.name: Ekans
card9.description: Moves silently and stealthily. Eats the eggs of birds, such as PIDGEY and SPEAROW, whole.

card10.name: Umbreon
card10.description: When exposed to the moon’s aura, the rings on its body glow faintly and it gains a mysterious power.

card11.name: Rapidash
card11.description: It gallops at nearly 150 mph. With its mane blazing ferociously, it races as if it were an arrow.

card12.name: Abra
card12.description: This Pokémon uses its psychic powers while it sleeps. The contents of Abra’s dreams affect the powers that the Pokémon wields.

card13.name: Cubone
card13.description: This Pokémon wears the skull of its deceased mother. Sometimes Cubone’s dreams make it cry, but each tear Cubone sheds makes it stronger.

card14.name: Clefairy
card14.description: It is said that happiness will come to those who see a gathering of Clefairy dancing under a full moon.

card16.name: Miraidon
card16.description: Much remains unknown about this creature. It resembles Cyclizar, but it is far more ruthless and powerful.

card17.name: Chien-Pao
card17.description: This Pokémon can control 100 tons of fallen snow. It plays around innocently by leaping in and out of avalanches it has caused.

card18.name: Cetoddle
card18.description: This species left the ocean and began living on land a very long time ago. It seems to be closely related to Wailmer.

card19.name: Palafin
card19.description: This Pokémon changes its appearance if it hears its allies calling for help. Palafin will never show anybody its moment of transformation.

card20.name: Wartortle
card20.description: It cleverly controls its furry ears and tail to maintain its balance while swimming.

card21.name: Butterfree
card21.description: It loves the nectar of flowers and can locate flower patches that have even tiny amounts of pollen.

card22.name: Iron Valiant
card22.description: It’s possible that this is the object listed as Iron Valiant in a certain expedition journal.

card23.name: Dragonite
card23.description: It is said that somewhere in the ocean lies an island where these gather. Only they live there.

card24.name: Eevee
card24.description: Its ability to evolve into many forms allows it to adapt smoothly and perfectly to any environment.

card25.name: Jigglypuff
card25.description: When its huge eyes waver, it sings a mysteriously soothing melody that lulls its enemies to sleep.
